HEADWORD: Calumniation
<hw>Ca*lum`ni*a"tion</hw>
<pr>(k⟦adot⟧*l⟦ucr⟧m`n⟦icr⟧*⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>False accusation of crime or offense, or a malicious and false
representation of the words or actions of another, with a view to injure
his good name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>calumniation</qex> of her principal counselors.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Calumniator</ent>⟦br⟧
